1. DEFINITIONS

"Software" means the source code, documentation, configuration files, and any
other material distributed under this license.

"Personal Use" means use of the Software exclusively for private, educational,
learning, or hobby purposes, by a natural person acting on their own behalf
and not on behalf of any organization or legal entity.

"Non-Profit Organization" means any entity, association, foundation, or
institution formally recognized as non-profit under the applicable law of the
relevant jurisdiction, and which uses the Software exclusively for its own
institutional activities.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software intended, directly or
indirectly, to generate revenue, reduce operational costs, support business
activities, or integrate the Software into products, services, or workflows
of a for-profit organization. This includes, without limitation:

  a) use of the Software within a company, professional firm, or for-profit
     entity, even for internal purposes only and even where the Software is
     not directly sold or redistributed;
  b) providing services to clients through or by means of the Software;
  c) integrating the Software into a commercial product;
  d) use of the Software by freelancers or independent contractors in the
     course of their billed professional activities.

